<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">Prayer for Easter</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Apr 16, 2017 00:00</p>
</header> <div class="org-center">

 <figure id="orgdf2bb57"> <img src="../images/posts/20170416-weeping-mary.jpg" alt="20170416-weeping-mary.jpg" width="100%"></img></figure></div>

 <p>
<small>
(Photograph:  <b>Weeping Mary</b> by Martin Gommel) <sup> <a id="fnr.1" class="footref" href="#fn.1" role="doc-backlink">1</a></sup>
</small>
</p>

 <p>
“Who is it you are looking for?” <br></br>
is a question for me, <br></br>
not just for Mary.
</p>

 <p>
Mary looked at Jesus, and saw the gardener.
</p>

 <p>
I look at my <br></br>
neighbor, and see a stranger; <br></br>
a stranger, an see an antagonist; <br></br>
an antagonist, and see an enemy.
</p>

 <p>
Help me, Lord, to see you, <br></br>
wherever, and whoever, you are.
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>





